ctionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529954\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mkb1665702870795.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mkb1665702870795.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mkb1665702870795.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mkb1665702870795\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n              \n Triggers for Processing User Events \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"mkb1665702870795__triggers_for_processing_user_events_84337\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">In desktop applications, an end user can activate triggers by pressing a key, choosing a menu option, or invoking macros to request an action. If the context is appropriate, the related trigger is fired.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mkb1665702870795__p_d25040e1_d25041e1_d25042e1\">For example, pressing <span class=\"ph keypress\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Ctrl+S</span></span> invokes the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">^STORE</span> macro,\n         causing Uniface to perform any outstanding data validation checks. If any of these return\n         an error, the store trigger is not activated.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Triggers Activated by Structure Editor Functions</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__1\">\n Trigger\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__2\">\n Level\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ppz1665702665163.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ppz1665702665163.html\" title=\"Interactive trigger that defines the application-wide actions in response to the ^SWITCH_KEY action, such as loading a new keyboard translation table.\">trigger keyboardSwitch</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__2\">\n Application\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"niy1665702606431.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/niy1665702606431.html\" title=\"Trigger for responding to user-defined key sequences as defined in the Keyboard Translation Table (KTT) or defined in the usys.ini section named as userkeys.\">trigger userKey</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__2\">\n Application and component\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xye1665702608643.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xye1665702608643.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to a request for a menu in a desktop application.\">trigger menu</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__2\">\n Application, component, entity, and field\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kez1665702582531.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kez1665702582531.html\" title=\"Handles processing when an Accept request is received, usually with the intention of closing the component and keeping all changes made on it. This trigger is exposed as an operation in the component signature.\">trigger accept</a>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aag1665703130023.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aag1665703130023.html\" title=\"Trigger that reacts to the user's request to start over with a clean form.\">trigger clear</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"two1665703130263.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/two1665703130263.html\" title=\"Trigger that deletes all occurrences currently in the component, both in the external structure, and in the database. This is a very dangerous trigger—use it with extreme care!\">trigger erase</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ita1665703130455.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ita1665703130455.html\" title=\"Interactive trigger for responding to a print request.\">trigger print</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qun1665702582075.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qun1665702582075.html\" title=\"Trigger that handles processing when a Quit request is received, usually with the intention of closing the component without saving any modifications made in it. This trigger is exposed as an operation in the component signature.\">trigger quit</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hmh1665703130535.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hmh1665703130535.html\" title=\"Location for ProcScript that retrieves data from the database.\">trigger retrieve</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jno1665702661208.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jno1665702661208.html\" title=\"Trigger that retrieves the next occurrence in the database with a primary key value greater than the current one.\">trigger retrieveSequential</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jvb1665703130778.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvb1665703130778.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to a request to save (store) the data.\">trigger store</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__2\">\n Component\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qzx1665702660750.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qzx1665702660750.html\" title=\"Trigger that handles a user’s request to add or insert a new occurrence of the entity in a Form.\">trigger create</a>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ncc1665702661055.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ncc1665702661055.html\" title=\"Location for ProcScript that marks an occurrence for deletion.\">trigger remove</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__2\">\n Entity\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"viq1665702608478.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/viq1665702608478.html\" title=\"Trigger for reacting to the user's request for online help in a desktop application.\">trigger help</a>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bqj1665702585000.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bqj1665702585000.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to an interactive event on a field or entity widget, such as the user clicking on the field.\">trigger detail</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__2\">\n Entity and field\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bkj1665702660842.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bkj1665702660842.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to a request for the next field in a form component.\">trigger next</a>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"umg1665702660913.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/umg1665702660913.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to a request for the previous field in a form component.\">trigger previous</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mkb1665702870795__table_d2705e1_d2706e1_d2707e1__entry__2\">\n Field\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529954\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529954\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Triggers for Processing User Events Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Triggers for Processing User Events In desktop applications, an end user can activate triggers by pressing a key, choosing a menu option, or invoking macros to request an action. If the context is appropriate, the related trigger is fired. For example, pressing Ctrl+S invokes the ^STORE macro, causing Uniface to perform any outstanding data validation checks. If any of these return an error, the store trigger is not activated. Table 1. Triggers Activated by Structure Editor Functions Trigger Level trigger keyboardSwitch Application trigger userKey Application and component trigger menu Application, component, entity, and field trigger accept trigger clear trigger erase trigger print trigger quit trigger retrieve trigger retrieveSequential trigger store Component trigger create trigger remove Entity trigger help trigger detail Entity and field trigger next trigger previous Field Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}